<TITLE> BFF to hold open trial for U-23 team </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 4 (bdnews24.com)  The Bangladesh Football Federation on Wednesday decided to hold an open trial in a bid to form an under-23 team for the 2010 South Asian Games in Bangladesh. The decision was taken by the national team management committee with committee chairman and BFF vice-president Badal Roy in the chair. The seven-day trial will get underway on March 7 at the Bangladesh Krira Shikkha Protisthan with Brazilian coach Edson Silva Dido being appointed head selector. Roy said the footballers from the different age-group teams, BKSP and B League clubs will join some 30 selected players in the trial. The meeting also decided to announce the preliminary national squad for the AFC Challenge Cup in the middle of the March 7 to 27 Super Cup. Roy, a former national player, said that they would consider the players' performances in the B League and upcoming Super Cup before picking the national side. He also said there were plans to start the national team camp from March 30. bd
